  "description": "¶Entry conditions Use typed lambda calculus when you need:\nA formal language for defining functions, applying them to arguments, and composing them. A type system that prevents ill-formed combinations (applying a number to a number, for instance). A bridge between logic and computation, where types correspond to propositions and terms correspond to proofs. ¶The untyped lambda calculus The untyped lambda calculus begins with three operations [@barendregt_LambdaCalculus_1984]:\n",
